revision.text:
{{Infobox theatre group | name = Blackout Improv | image = | imagesize = | caption = | formed = 2015 | disbanded = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | genre = [[Improvisational comedy]] | location = [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]] | members = | ArtisticDirector = | notable = | homepage = {{URL|https://www.blackoutcomedy.org/}} }}
'''Blackout Improv''' is an [[improvisational comedy]] theatre troupe in [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.phoenixtheatermpls.org/project/blackout/ | title = Blackout | website = Phoenix Theater Minneapolis | accessdate = September 26, 2017 }}</ref> Founded in 2015, the cast is completely [[African Americans|black]]. Topics of monthly comedy performances include standard improv audience suggestions as well as a special focus on civil rights issues like [[police brutality]], [[white privilege]], and [[cultural appropriation]].<ref name = gibney2017>{{cite magazine | title = Brave Black Workshop | date = December 2017 | last = Gibney | first = Shannon | magazine = [[Mpls.St.Paul Magazine]] }}</ref> Blackout Improv responded to the [[shooting of Jamar Clark]]<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.twincities.com/2016/07/28/blackout-improv-comedy-troupe-obama-out/ | title = Blackout Improv strives to shed comedic light on what’s not so funny | newspaper = [[St. Paul Pioneer Press]] | date = July 28, 2016 | accessdate = September 26, 2017 | last = Hewitt | first = Chris }}</ref> as well as the acquittal of police officer Jeronimo Yanez after the [[shooting of Philando Castile]].<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.mprnews.org/story/2017/09/20/blackout-improv-celebrates-anniversary | agency = [[Minnesota Public Radio]] | title = At Blackout Improv, comedy wrestles with tragedy | date = September 20, 2017 | last = Combs | first = Marianne| accessdate = September 26, 2017}}</ref>
Blackout Improv, along with efforts like the Black and Funny Improv Festival,<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.startribune.com/blackout-improv-troupe-shows-sparks-of-genius-in-new-griots-festival-at-guthrie/433664783/ | newspaper = [[Minneapolis Star Tribune]] | last = Preston | first = Rohan | title = Blackout Improv troupe shows sparks of genius in New Griots Festival at Guthrie | accessdate = September 26, 2017}}</ref> are bringing more people of color to Twin Cities improv theater.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.startribune.com/a-black-man-s-crusade-to-diversify-the-twin-cities-improv-scene/416945154/ | newspaper = [[Minneapolis Star Tribune]] | date = March 24, 2017 | accessdate = September 26, 2017 | last = Ross | first = Jenna | title = Black comedian crusades to diversify the Twin Cities improv scene }}</ref> Blackout Improv performs at the [[Mixed Blood Theatre]] in [[Cedar-Riverside, Minneapolis]].<ref name=gibney2017/>
