{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2013}} {{Infobox person |name=Karen Moncrieff |birth_date={{birth date and age|1963|12|20}} |birth_place=[[Sacramento]], California |occupation=Film director, screenwriter }}
'''Karen Moncrieff''' (born December 20, 1963 in [[Sacramento]], California), is an American actress, director and screenwriter. Her directorial debut was ''[[Blue Car]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Blue Car (2002) FILM REVIEW; Teacher and Prodigy, Along With Need and Lust|first=Stephen|last=Holden|date=May 2, 2003|url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9F03E4DC163CF931A35756C0A9659C8B63|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref>
Her directing credits are in both television and [[feature film|features]] and she acted in the soap operas ''[[Passions]]'', ''[[Days of Our Lives]]'' and ''[[Santa Barbara (TV series)|Santa Barbara]]''. In 1985, she was crowned [[Miss Illinois]] and competed in the [[Miss America 1986]] pageant. Karen graduated from [[Rochester Adams High School]] in 1982, the same high school Madonna attended.
== Filmography == *''[[Wings (NBC TV series)|Wings]]'' (1994) as Deidre *''[[Blue Car]]'' (2002) – Director/Writer *''[[Six Feet Under (TV series)|Six Feet Under]]'' (2003) (TV series) *''[[Touching Evil]]'' (2004) (TV Series) *''[[The Dead Girl]]'' (2007) – Director/Writer *''[[The Trials of Cate McCall]]'' (2013) – Director/Producer/Writer *''[[The Keeping Hours]]'' (2017) - Director
