{{short description|journal}} {{Infobox journal | title = Theatre Journal | cover = Theatre journal.gif | formernames = Educational Theatre Journal | editor = Ric Knowles, Ph.D. | discipline = [[Performing arts]] | abbreviation = Theatre J. | publisher = [[Johns Hopkins University Press]] | country = United States | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1949-present | openaccess = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.press.jhu.edu/journals/theatre_journal/ | link1 = http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/tj/ | link1-name = Online access at [[Project MUSE]] | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 33895455 | LCCN = 79643622 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0192-2882 | eISSN = 1086-332X }} The '''''Theatre Journal''''' is a quarterly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering the [[theatre arts]],<ref>{{cite journal |title=Publication Information |journal=Theatre Journal |date=December 2014 |volume=66 |issue=4 |page=ii}}</ref> with articles from the October and December issues centering on a predetermined theme. It is an official publication of [[The Association for Theatre in Higher Education]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Theatre Journal |url=http://www.press.jhu.edu/journals/theatre_journal/ |publisher=Johns Hopkins University Press}}</ref> and is published on their behalf by the [[Johns Hopkins University Press]].
== History == The journal was established in 1949 as the ''Educational Theatre Journal'' and obtained its current name in 1979.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Front Matter |journal=Theatre Journal |date=March 1979 |volume=31 |issue=1 |pages=1}}</ref> The American Educational Theatre Association intended the journal to serve the field of educational theatre and drama in a manner similar to how the ''[[Quarterly Journal of Speech]]'' and ''[[Publications of the Modern Language Association of America]]'' served the fields of speech and modern languages respectively.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Hewitt |first1=Barnard |title=Editor's Foreword |journal=Educational Theatre Journal |date=October 1949 |volume=1 |issue=1 |page=1}}</ref> The founding [[editor-in-chief|Editor-in-Chief]] was [[Barnard Hewitt]] ([[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]]). Other past editors include [[Sue-Ellen Case]], Susan Bennett, and [[Jean Graham-Jones]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Theatre Journal: Journal Information |url=http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/theatre_journal/ |publisher=[[Project Muse]]}}</ref>
== Abstracting and indexing == The journal is abstracted and indexed in: {{columns-list|colwidth=30em| * [[Academic OneFile]] * [[Academic Search Premier]] * [[Arts and Humanities Citation Index]] * [[Bibliography of Asian Studies]] * [[InfoTrac]] * [[International Index to the Performing Arts]] * [[ProQuest|ProQuest databases]] * [[VINITI Database RAS]] * [[Scopus]] }}
